        <p class="large note panel">
          <strong>DESIGN DECISION</strong>
        </p>
        <div class="center">
          <div class="grid-thirds">
            <p class="small note">
              <strong>User-Centered Design</strong>
              <br>
              Due to gesture researchers' heavy concern of data confidentiality, we decided to implement an account signup/signin feature so users must login to use the application.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="grid-thirds">
            <p class="small note">
              <strong>User Control & Freedom</strong>
              <br>
              Visualization is directly manipulative. Users may click and drag the visualization to a different angle. In addition, they may also zoom in/out to get a better view of the data. 
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="grid-thirds">
            <p class="small note">
              <strong>Minimalist Design</strong>
              <br>
              Minimal content on each process stage to keep a simple and clean look, and making the advanced filtering options collapsable helps minimizing clusterness of contents.
            </p>
            
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="center">
          <div class="grid-thirds">
            <p class="small note">
              <strong>User Control & Freedom</strong>
              <br>
              Upload feature for users to work on any Kinect CSV file that they wish. It accepts 2D (x-y corrdinate points) or 3D (x-y-z coordinate points).
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="grid-thirds">
            <p class="small note">
              <strong>Error Prevention</strong>
              <br>
              Force users to upload only Kinect generated CSV format file, and it will only proceed to the visualization if the format is correct.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="grid-thirds">
            <p class="small note">
              <strong>Help Users Recover from Errors</strong>
              <br>
              Error messages will pop up if the wrong type of file is selected for uploading. The selected file's name will also be displayed on the page.  
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="center">
          <div class="grid-thirds">
            <p class="small note">
              <strong>User Control & Freedom</strong>
              <br>
              Data filtering options near the visualization further provide data customizability and manipulation. 
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="grid-thirds">
            <p class="small note">
              <strong>Flexibility and Efficiency of Use</strong>
              <br>
              Consistent navbar that provides each stage of process reduces time for users to recover from mistakes.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="grid-thirds">
            <p class="small note">
              <strong>Recognition rather than Recall</strong>
              <br>
              A message is next to the "Choose File" to remind user's interaction - what file they selected.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
